# EEG Attention Analysis

This project analyzes EEG data to identify neural signatures of attention.

## Project Overview
- Compare EEG during rest vs task (mental arithmetic)
- Extract band power features (theta, alpha, beta)
- Evaluate statistical differences using bootstrap confidence intervals
- Build classification models to detect attention states

## Key Findings (so far)
- Alpha power shows a consistent decrease during task engagement
- Theta shows weak or inconsistent effects
- Beta shows a small but consistent decrease

## Dataset
- PhysioNet EEG During Mental Arithmetic Tasks

## Next Steps
- Build classification model
- Test generalization on second dataset